@node "Slijmen" "Free Registering"
@toc "ImpressieMaken"
                             @{b}@{u}Registration info@{ub}@{uu}


 ** SORRY TO THOSE REGISTERED AFTER SEP 96, BUT I WAS QUITE BUSY - THOSE
    WHO DID NOT RECEIVE AN EMAIL-PRESENT SHOULD CONTACT ME AGAIN !! **

 @{u}How do you register ?@{uu}

 DiskSqueeze  is  @{i}'pictureware'@{ui},  which means  that you'll have to send a
 picture to me (in digital format - ANY format is OK (PCX/GIF/IFF/JPG/PCD))
 of something weird or nice... (a nice chick is a (very) good suggestion ;-)
 Include a list of your current computer setup aswell

 (judged from what I already received, there are some sick minds around :-)

 Snail mail is OK, although I prefer e-mail for fast replies...

 See @{"Author" link "Stoefen" 0} for all the address stuph...


 @{u}What do you get for this picture in return ?@{uu}

 - FAST & longlife updates/bugfixes/hints/help/etc (e-mail only)
 - some interesting mail now and then about new Amiga developments (e-mail
   only)
 - a 'binary' surprise... 8-)
 - you become a beta-tester for future DSQs, but only if you want to


 To magazines:

 please notice me by email if a review is made, or send me a copy of the
 issue if you're including this program on a coverCD/disk
 For the rest I do not need anything... it's just freeware you know.

 Other reasons to contact me:

 you have a lot of @{b}garage underground-house music@{ub}, and like to swap some
 cool tracks on MC, CD or MD (I have over 1700 CDs and 300 12")
 I'm still looking for tracks like "Fibre Foundation - free your mind"
 or "DJ Device - positive influences EP 1" or "Disco Elements - EP 3" or
 "Markus Life  - Life will make you dance" on Class-X-Recordings, Grant
 Nelson or Danny Tenaglia remix cuts.

 you are a @{b}Level 42@{ub} fan : I'm still missing some live performances and
 remixes.  I can supply you with alot of rare material (even CD video
 material) on MC, CD or MD.  Just send me a list of what you got, and
 I'll be grateful to reply in a generous way, if you have something I don't
@endnode

